  "commentary": "With SPX at 6758 sitting above the GEX flip (6718) but caught between massive negative gamma at 6750 (-11.8B) and positive gamma at 6775 (+8.0B), dealers are in a precarious hedging position where they're forced to buy any dip toward 6750 and sell any rally toward 6775. The breakout regime with -123.6M total GEX means dealers are amplifying moves in both directions, creating a volatile 25-point trading range between these key strikes. The gex_surge event combined with dealers being short gamma suggests we're likely to see violent whipsaws as spot oscillates between the 6750 buy zone and 6775 sell zone.\n\nBottom line: expect violent swings between 6750 and 6775 as dealers chase the moves.",
